            <h5 class="w3-center w3-padding-64"><span class="w3-tag w3-wide">ABOUT THE GAME</span></h5>
            <p> BePresent system uses a game for the students to motivate them to attend school consistently and on time. It is designed to peak students’ interests using engaging visual experiences. Students will earn Reward Points by attending school consistently. Then, Students can use the Reward Points to access the immersive 3D image post-cards of the cities around the world. </p>
            <p>We leverages AR technologies to create stunning visual experiences that virtually transport the user to a new city. We plan to use these experiences to educate students about diverse cultures and people around the world. They can interact with the visuals using touch to explore various aspects of the visual and learn more about them. </p>
            <p>Besides great virtual experiences,  the student who holds most post-cards at the end of quarter will be the winner of the game. Final winner might also get real-word reward from administrators. </p>
